\begin_layout Subsection
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Channel input state registers
\end_layout

\end_inset

Status register
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Register 
\series default
18(0x12) - Status register.
 Read/Write.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Register 
\series default
19(0x13) - Reserved.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The lower five bits each represent an I/O channel with I/O-1 on bit 0 an
 so on.
 Writing a value to a position that is configured as an output will set
 that output to a high or low depending on the value written.
 Writing to an input will not effect it.
 Reading the status register will read the actual output state for outputs
 and the input value for I/O channels configured as inputs.
\end_layout

