\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Register 
\series default
67(0x43) – Reserved.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is the pulse time for the each I/O channel expressed in seconds.
 This can be used to have an I/O channel set as an output to turn on and
 off with a certain preset interval.
 The minimum pulse time is 1 second and the maximum time is 65535 seconds
 which is about 18 hours.
 Set to zero (default) for no pulse time i.e.
 the relay will be steady on/off.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To start a pulse sequence bit 0 for the corresponding relay should be set
 to one.
\end_layout

